  <scene-outline>
    **Scene 1: False Wisdom** (~1800 words)
    Days after Elder Heartwood disappointment. Hostile plant activity increasing—scouts report organized opposition, possibly planning action against facility. Group discusses how to respond. Florence offers "Elder Twist's counsel" about de-escalating conflict with hostile neighbors, seems wise and reasonable. Plans made based on this guidance. Then Elder Twist speaks (delayed response to unrelated question from days earlier) and it's completely different from what Florence claimed—makes it obvious Florence has been fabricating.

    **Scene 2: The Deception** (~2000 words)
    Confrontation. How long has this been going on? Plants reviewing past "Elder Twist wisdom," realizing most was Florence's fabrication. Florence defensive at first, then confesses: wanted to help, had good instincts, but didn't believe anyone would value HER judgment, so used Elder Twist's authority. Her advice WAS sound! But plants feel betrayed—it's not about whether advice was good, it's about honesty and trust. Florence tries to justify, makes things worse. Holloway especially hurt (another authority failure, but this time from within). Florence's isolation begins.

    **Scene 3: Broken Trust** (~1800 words)
    Aftermath of revelation. Plants processing betrayal, Florence withdrawn and isolated. Kira attempts to mediate—recognizes Florence's judgment was actually valuable, points out the advice helped even if source was false. Plants can't accept this yet: trust matters more than utility, how do they move forward if they can't be honest with each other? Florence guilty but also resentful (she WAS right, her advice DID help). Hostile plant threats still looming. Group fractured at worst possible time. Ends with recognition: they need to resolve this, but no one knows how yet. Trust harder to build than to break.
  </scene-outline>
